# Copy to .env.local and fill in. Do not commit secrets.
#
# --- Phase 1 (production) checklist ---
# [ ] NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL = your canonical origin (no trailing slash)
# [ ] All NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_* vars set (see Firebase console)
# [ ] NEWSLETTER_FORM_ACTION = Formspree (or compatible) URL if using footer signup
# [ ] Optional: NEXT_PUBLIC_SOCIAL_* for footer icons
# [ ] GitHub Actions: repository Variables → NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL for accurate sitemap in CI
# [ ] Vercel: Project → Settings → Environment Variables — mirror .env.local for Preview and Production.
#     Build requires NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY, AUTH_DOMAIN, PROJECT_ID, APP_ID (see src/lib/env.ts).
#     Set NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL to your production origin (no trailing slash), e.g. https://your-app.vercel.app
#
# Install tip: repo .npmrc uses include=dev so eslint/jest always install.

# Used for canonical URLs, OG metadata, and blog JSON-LD (no trailing slash)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Optional explicit app origin for server-side PDF print route.
# If unset, export falls back to NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:9002

# Server-only: newsletter forward target (e.g. Formspree). JSON POST body: { "email": "..." }
# In production, if this is unset the API returns 503 (newsletter_not_configured).
# NEWSLETTER_FORM_ACTION=https://formspree.io/f/your-form-id

# Optional public social links (footer). Omit any you don’t use — the link is hidden if unset.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SOCIAL_X=https://x.com/yourhandle
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SOCIAL_LINKEDIN=https://www.linkedin.com/company/yourco
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SOCIAL_INSTAGRAM=https://www.instagram.com/yourhandle

# Optional: Sentry browser DSN — Web Vitals → Sentry metrics (uses @sentry/browser + @sentry/nextjs)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=

# --- Phase 3 (done in repo): perf & quality gates ---
# npm run verify  → lint + typecheck + jest
# npm run lhci    → Lighthouse CI (after build + from fitcvv1)
# Playwright: e2e/ smoke + editor; webServer NODE_ENV=development, 180s timeout
# Core Web Vitals → Sentry metrics when NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN is set
#
# --- Phase 4 (growth & ops) ---
# [ ] Optional GA4: set NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID and load gtag in layout (or GTM → dataLayer)
# [ ] Monitor GET /api/health (JSON { ok, service, time }) from uptime tools
# [ ] Use trackEvent() from @/lib/analytics-events for key conversions (newsletter already tracked)

# Optional Google Analytics 4 — loads gtag from layout + CSP allowlist in next.config.mjs
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# Optional PostHog analytics
# NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY=phc_xxx
# NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST=https://app.posthog.com

# Optional Razorpay checkout (if unset, pricing keeps free-upgrade path)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=rzp_test_xxx
# RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=rzp_test_xxx
# RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET=your_server_secret
# RAZORPAY_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret
# RAZORPAY_PRO_AMOUNT_PAISE=29900
# RAZORPAY_CURRENCY=INR

# Firebase / Genkit / AI keys — set in .env.local per your deployment docs
#
# --- Local test account (email/password auth) ---
# Recommended demo user (not created automatically):
#   Email:    demo@fitcv.test
#   Password: FitCV-Demo-2024!
# Create it once: /signup with the values above, or Firebase Console → Authentication → Add user.
# In development, the login page shows “Fill demo credentials” and the (i) tooltip lists the same.
